properties.areaDesc: Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued March 1 at 2:39PM PST until March 3 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 20 to 30 kt.

* WHERE...Northern Inland Waters Including The San Juan Islands.

* WHEN...From 1 AM Monday to 4 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM MONDAY TO 4 AM PST TUESDAY
